1 (A) HOW MANY STUDENTS ARE ENROLLED IN THE SCHOOL;
2 (B) THE NUMBER OF ENROLLED STUDENTS WITH VACCINE EXEMPTIONS;
3 (C) THE NUMBER OF FULLY VACCINATED STUDENTS; AND
4 (D) THE NUMBER OF STUDENTS WITH CONDITIONAL ENROLLMENT."
5
6 Section 2. Section 20-5-408, MCA, is amended to read:
7 "20-5-408. Enforcement. (1) The governing authority of any school other than a postsecondary
8 school shall prohibit from further attendance any pupil student allowed to attend conditionally who has failed to
9 obtain the immunizations required by 20-5-403(1) within time periods established by the department until that
10 pupil student has been immunized as required by the department or unless that pupil student has been
11 exempted under 20-5-405.
12 (2) The governing authority shall conform with the provisions of the Family Educational Rights and
13 Privacy Act of 1974, 20 U.S.C. 1232g, as amended, and its implementing regulations at 34 CFR, part 99.
14 (3) A student's health records, including information related to immunizations received and
15 immunization exemptions, are considered part of the student's education record and are protected from
16 disclosure as provided in the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act of 1974."
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
